CHANGES0048 - SeqColimWork.agda: Sequential colimit closure formalization

New file: SeqColimWork.agda (364 lines, compiles, 3 postulate blocks)

Translated from Spectral/colimit/seq_colim.hlean (Lean/hlean formalization by
Floris van Doorn and Egbert Rijke) and the paper by Sojakova, van Doorn, Rijke
"Sequential Colimits in Homotopy Type Theory" (LICS 2020).

PROVEN:
- seqCo recursive colimit definition (avoids ℕ-arithmetic via ShiftSeq)
- ShiftEquiv: shift equivalence (lift is an equiv), lemShift
- Fi, Fg: maps from SeqColim → seqCo (by structural recursion on ℕ)
- toRecursive, fromRecursive: maps between SeqColim and seqCo
- fromTo: fromRecursive ∘ toRecursive ≡ id (on SeqColim)
  - fromToFi, fromToFg helper lemmas
- equivSeqCo: Iso (SeqColim A) (seqCo A) (modulo toFrom postulate)
- colimitContr: seqCo of contractible types is contractible
  (via library's converges→ColimIso + equivSeqCo)
- code_i, code_g, code: the type family (B∞) over seqCo
- sigmaSequence, liftCodeEq
- fwdF: forward map seqCo(ΣSeq) → Σ(seqCo A)(code)
- bwdG0, bwdG: backward map Σ(seqCo A)(code) → seqCo(ΣSeq)
- SigmaColim module: sigmaColimit Iso (modulo FG-full, GF-full)
- ySSeq: path fibration (identity type as a SeqFib)
- sigmaYContr: Σ of path fibration is contractible
- sigmaCodeContr: code-Σ version contractible
- colimitPaths: (inj x ≡ y) ≃ code(ySSeq x)(y) -- MAIN THEOREM
  paths in sequential colimits are sequential colimits of paths
- Transfer to library SeqColim: sigmaColimitLib, colimitPathsLib

POSTULATED (3 blocks):
1. toFrom (line 146): toRecursive ∘ fromRecursive ≡ id on seqCo
   Issue: lift case needs ∙ of toRec-liftSC and cong lift (IH),
   but refl ∙ refl ≠ refl definitionally at gl boundary.

2. FG-full (line 273): bwdG ∘ fwdF ≡ id on seqCo(ΣSeq)
   The gl case requires showing comp in bwdG0's gl case
   produces gl(a,b). Complex cubical cube computation.

3. GF-full (line 287): fwdF ∘ bwdG ≡ id on Σ(seqCo A)(code)
   Double induction. The (inj a, lift y) case needs ΣPathP with
   base sym(gl a); the (gl a i, y) case involves bwdG0's gl case.
